reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 19, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Motherboard DOA, Poor support from Manufacturer
reviews.reviewText: I opened a web ticket with MSI and and got a quick response telling me to update BIOS. I responded stating I cannot update the BIOS as the computer fails POST and does not boot. Even when I google ways to update the BIOS on MSI, everything states to enter BIOS. I get no video from the onboard video so I can't see if I am entering BIOS setup or not. Have not heard a thing from MSI support since. POOR Support in my eyes.I have never had an issue with the seller. In fact I really miss living by one like I did a few years ago. The MSI motherboard does not Post, all I get is red/yellow blinking lights before stopping yellow. Which points to RAM. The RAM I purchased is listed as acceptable RAM on MSI list of approved RAM. So I bought more RAM (never hurts having more) and same issue. Registration of the motherboard is horrible with the manufacturer as you have to create an account and they share your information with a 3rd party advertising agency so I am giving my email and name to someone who is going to inundate me with SPAM. I am so sorry I went with MSI. And I will never do that again. I have always used a different brand, but I wanted to save money (had I still lived near the sellers store I could have bought the brand of MB I prefer, gotten the processor I got and the RAM I got as a bundle) but since they do not do online sales other than through here, I was limited and could not get a break on the RAM. Lesson learned: You get what you pay for. I am so disgusted with MSI over the registration that I am dreading trying to file a warranty claim. I wish I could just send this board back and buy the brand I prefer as the RAM I have is on their list too.
